================
**Government Tender Announcement: W684Q-240206**

### Tenders Closing Date and Time

The [Department of Public Works and Government Services](https://www.tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca/) invites qualified bidders to submit proposals for the provision of Pest Control Services under the Contract W684Q-240206.

 bids and proposals must be submitted electronically through the [Government Electronic Tendering System (GETS)](https://buyandsell.gc.ca/gts) by February 14th, 2024, at 14:00 hours EST.

### Notice Details

*   **Request Identification Number:** WS4314518578
*   **NAICS Code:** 72102100
*   **Procurement Category:** SRV
*   **Procurement Method:** NON-OLB Competitive Bidding
*   **Use of Trade Agreements:** Yes, Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA)
Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA)
Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)
Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement - Expired (sunset clause)
Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA) - Expired (sunset clause)
Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP)
Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement - Expired (sunset clause)
Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement - Expired (sunset clause)
World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)

### End User

*   **Entity:** Department of National Defence (DND)
*   **Contact:** Christine Cress (SPAC/PSPC)
    CHRISTINE.CRESS@TPSGC.PWGSC.GC.CA

### Service Description

Pest control services are required for the following regions:
*   British Columbia
 Procurement Category is SRV and the procurement method is Non-OLB Competitive Bidding.

The Successful tenderer will be notified and asked to execute a contract in accordance with the tender document. Further information about the Goods and Services can be found in the electronic document available through the link below.
The Contracting Entity is Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC).
    = The Service location is Province of British Columbia.

Per your guidelines no general information will be provided about past experience.
